main event: An object similar to a large star was observed over the horizon at a speed of 2,500 mph on 5 January 1963.
interesting points: The object was described as a pin-point of light observed for 1 minute.,The object was heading approximately 5 degrees south of due east.,The estimated altitude of the object was around 5 miles.,It was observed by two employees from a nearby location.,The report mentions that NORADS/ADC ruled out known satellite schedules.
sighted object: a pin-point of light resembling a large star
